  <brief_title>Gait Disturbances and Hips Bone Mineral Density</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to investigate the role of gait disturbance as a cause for
      difference in Bone Mineral Density (BMD) between both hips. Each subject will undergo the
      following tests: Functional Mobility Testing, Gait analysis, Motion Analysis, Assessments for
      Balance and Gait and Cognitive assessments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
